mputation\n\n---\n\n**Collection Purpose**: This collection preserves seminal works in modern cryptography, from the birth of public-key cryptography to state-of-the-art implementations. Together, these papers tell the story of how cryptography evolved from a military secret to an essential technology protecting billions of people's privacy and security every day.\n\n**Curator**: Collected 2026-01-03 for cyberspace library on distributed systems security and cryptographic protocols.\n\n**Last Updated**: 2026-01-04\n") (papers "1. Diffie-Hellman (~260 KB, 1 paper)" "2. Daniel J. Bernstein (djb) (~3.2 MB, 8 papers)" "3. Bruce Schneier (~1 MB, 2 papers)" "4. Philip Zimmermann (~1.3 MB, 2 documents)" "5. SSH Designers (~220 KB, 4 RFCs)" "6. Steven M. Bellovin (~810 KB, 4 papers)" "7. Matt Blaze (~5.1 MB, 5 papers)" "8. David Chaum (~1.8 MB, 4 papers)" "9. Donald Eastlake (~280 KB, 4 RFCs)" "10. Butler Lampson (~700 KB, 5 papers)" "11. Charlie Kaufman (~1 MB, 3 RFCs)" "12. Key Management Protocols (~1.2 MB, 12 RFCs and documents)" "13. Ralph Merkle (~13 MB, 5 papers)" "14. Post-Quantum Cryptography and Signatures (~10 MB, 9 papers and standards)" "15. Quantum Algorithms (~374 KB, 2 papers)" "16. NRL One-Time Passwords (~410 KB, 4 papers and RFCs)" "Public-Key Cryptography" "Stream Ciphers and Block Ciphers" "Hash Functions and MACs" "Security Analysis" "Network and Protocol Security" "Crypto Policy and Civil Liberties" "Key Management and Authentication" "Distributed Security Architecture" "TLS/HTTPS (Web Security)" "SSH (System Administration)" "VPNs (WireGuard)" "Messaging (Signal, WhatsApp)" "Email (PGP/GPG)" "For Cryptography Students" "For Security Professionals" "For Developers" "DSSA-NCSC Papers" "Lamport Papers" "SPKI" "Official Websites" "Standards Organizations" "Software Implementations" "Turing Award Winners (ACM)" "National Academy of Engineering" "Internet Hall of Fame" "National Cybersecurity Hall of Fame" "Other Recognition" "Books" "Papers Not in This Co