c theory (public key, Diffie-Hellman) and build practical, deployable protocols that solve real-world problems. The evolution from IKEv1 to IKEv2 shows the value of learning from deployment experience and simplifying when possible.\n\n---\n\n**Collection Notes**: Charlie Kaufman's contributions span distributed authentication (DASS, DSSA) to practical VPN security (IKE/IPsec). His work shows the progression from research systems (DSSA at DEC) to Internet standards (IKEv2) deployed globally. The IKEv2 protocol is a masterclass in protocol design: secure, practical, and simple enough to implement correctly.\n\n**Curator**: Collected 2026-01-03 for cyberspace library on distributed systems security and cryptographic protocols.\n") (papers "Distributed Authentication Security Service" "Internet Key Exchange Protocol Version 2" "Digital DSSA (1989)" "DASS (1993)" "IKEv1 (1998)" "IKEv2 (2005-2014)" "Purpose" "Key Features" "Authentication Methods" "Message Flow" "Digital Equipment Corporation (1980s)" "Lotus Development / IBM (1990s)" "Microsoft (2000s-2010s)" "\"Network Security: Private Communication in a Public World\"" "Book Impact" "IPsec Components" "IKE's Role" "Deployment" "Joint Work" "Complementary Expertise" "RFCs Authored/Edited" "Working Groups" "IAB Service" "IKE Vulnerabilities" "IKEv2 Improvements" "VPN Renaissance" "Cloud Security" "Standards Evolution" "DSSA Co-Authors" "Authentication Protocols" "Key Exchange" "Protocol Design") (years "2026" "1989" "1993" "2010" "2014" "1998" "2005" "1980" "1990" "2000" "1995" "2002" "2020" "1992" "2006") (authors "Charlie Kaufman - IPsec" "Overview\n\nCharlie Kaufman is a security architect best known as the principal designer of the Internet Key Exchange" "He co-authored the Digital Distributed System Security Architecture" "DEC in 1989" "DASS" "Network Security" "His work at DEC" "Kaufman" "Timestamp-based authentication" "Provide authentication services in a distributed environment that are both more secure and eas